# Client Development Guide

Comprehensive guide for React, PatternFly 6, and OpenShift-aligned UI development.

---

## 1. Component Architecture

### Component Types

| Type | Location | Purpose |
|------|----------|---------|
| **Pages** | `pages/` | Top-level route components. Fetch data via TanStack Query, compose layout. One per route. |
| **Feature components** | `components/<feature>/` | Domain-specific components grouped by feature (dashboard, releases, test-explorer). |
| **Common components** | `components/common/` | Reusable UI elements. Receive data via props, minimal internal state. |
| **Layout components** | `components/layout/` | App shell: Masthead, Sidebar, PageSection wrappers. |
| **Modals** | `components/modals/` | Self-contained dialogs with own form state and submission. |
| **Context providers** | `context/` | React contexts for cross-cutting concerns (auth, preferences, toasts). |

### File Structure

```
packages/client/src/
├── api/                    # API client functions (one file per resource)
│   ├── client.ts           # apiFetch, apiPost, ApiError
│   ├── launches.ts
│   └── ...
├── components/
│   ├── common/             # StatusBadge, PassRateBar, TimeAgo
│   ├── dashboard/          # DashboardGrid, LaunchCard
│   ├── detail/             # LogViewer, SimilarFailuresPanel
│   ├── layout/             # AppLayout, AppMasthead, AppSidebar
│   ├── modals/             # TriageModal, JiraCreateModal
│   ├── releases/           # VersionDashboard, ReleaseChecklist
│   ├── settings/           # ReportPortalSettings, JiraSettings
│   └── test-explorer/      # FileDetail, MonacoViewer
├── context/                # AuthContext, PreferencesContext, ToastContext
├── hooks/                  # useWebSocket, useDashboardFilters
├── pages/                  # DashboardPage, LaunchDetailPage, SettingsPage
├── styles/                 # app.css (custom styles using PF tokens)
└── utils/                  # Pure utility functions (cronHelpers, etc.)
```

### Naming Conventions

- Component files: **PascalCase** (`DashboardPage.tsx`, `StatusBadge.tsx`)
- API files: **camelCase** matching resource (`launches.ts`, `triage.ts`)
- Hook files: **camelCase** with `use` prefix (`useWebSocket.ts`)
- Context files: **PascalCase** matching context (`AuthContext.tsx`)
- Utility files: **camelCase** (`cronHelpers.ts`)

