## 8. CSS Conventions

### File Location

All custom CSS lives in `packages/client/src/styles/app.css`. No other CSS files.

### Class Naming

- **Utility classes**: `app-{property}-{size}` -- spacing (`app-mb-md`, `app-mt-lg`, `app-ml-sm`, `app-mr-xs`, `app-p-md`), typography (`app-text-sm`, `app-font-bold`), sizing (`app-min-w-200`, `app-max-w-400`, `app-w-full`), layout (`app-flex-center`, `app-full-height`)
- **Domain blocks**: `app-{feature}-{element}` -- e.g., `app-table-scroll`, `app-masthead-select`, `app-changelog-content`, `app-settings-vtabs`, `app-danger-zone`
- **State modifiers**: `app-{element}--{state}` -- e.g., `app-row--selected`, `app-cell--clickable`

### When to Add New CSS

1. Check if a PF utility class already exists (spacing, alignment, display)
2. Check if an existing `app-*` class covers your need
3. If neither, add a new class to `app.css` using PF tokens
4. NEVER create additional CSS files -- everything in `app.css`

### PF Overrides

Sometimes PatternFly components need slight adjustments. Use scoped selectors:

```css
.app-compact-table .pf-v6-c-table {
  --pf-v6-c-table--cell--PaddingTop: var(--pf-t--global--spacer--xs);
  --pf-v6-c-table--cell--PaddingBottom: var(--pf-t--global--spacer--xs);
}
```

- ALWAYS scope PF overrides under an `app-*` parent class
- Use PF component CSS variables (not PF internal class selectors) when possible
- NEVER use `!important`

