## 10. Context Pattern

### Standard Structure

```typescript
type MyContextValue = { /* ... */ };
const MyContext = createContext<MyContextValue | null>(null);

export const MyProvider = ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) => {
  // state, effects, logic
  const value = useMemo(() => ({ /* ... */ }), [deps]);
  return <MyContext.Provider value={value}>{children}</MyContext.Provider>;
};

export const useMy = (): MyContextValue => {
  const ctx = useContext(MyContext);
  if (!ctx) {
    throw new Error('useMy must be used within MyProvider');
  }
  return ctx;
};
```

Rules:
- Context value is `null` by default -- the hook throws if used outside provider
- Memoize the value object to prevent unnecessary re-renders
- Provider handles its own data fetching and side effects
- Export only the Provider component and the `useX` hook
- Nest providers in `main.tsx` in dependency order (outer providers don't depend on inner)

### Existing Contexts

| Context | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `AuthProvider` | User identity from `/api/user/profile`, `isAdmin` flag |
| `PreferencesProvider` | User preferences with debounced save (1s) to server |
| `ComponentFilterProvider` | Component filter state synced to URL params |
| `ToastProvider` | PF `AlertGroup` toasts with auto-dismiss (6s) |
| `DateProvider` | Lookback mode and date range for dashboard |

