## 11. Form Handling

No form library -- use controlled React state with PatternFly form components.

### Pattern

```tsx
const [name, setName] = useState('');
const [type, setType] = useState('Bug');

const mutation = useMutation({
  mutationFn: () => apiPost('/resource', { name, type }),
  onSuccess: () => {
    void queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['resources'] });
    onClose();
  },
});

return (
  <Form onSubmit={e => { e.preventDefault(); mutation.mutate(); }}>
    <FormGroup fieldId="name" isRequired label="Name">
      <TextInput id="name" isRequired onChange={(_e, val) => setName(val)} value={name} />
    </FormGroup>
    <FormGroup fieldId="type" label="Type">
      <FormSelect id="type" onChange={(_e, val) => setType(val)} value={type}>
        <FormSelectOption label="Bug" value="Bug" />
        <FormSelectOption label="Story" value="Story" />
      </FormSelect>
    </FormGroup>
    <Button isDisabled={mutation.isPending} isLoading={mutation.isPending} type="submit">
      Submit
    </Button>
  </Form>
);
```

Rules:
- Wrap in `<Form onSubmit>` with `e.preventDefault()`
- Use PF `FormGroup` with `label` and `fieldId` for accessibility
- PF input `onChange` signature: `(_event, value) => setState(value)`
- Disable submit button during mutation (`isDisabled={mutation.isPending}`)
- Show loading state on button (`isLoading={mutation.isPending}`)
- Invalidate related queries in `onSuccess`

