## 12. WebSocket Integration

### Client-Side Pattern

`useWebSocket` in `hooks/useWebSocket.ts`:
- Connects to `ws(s)://host/ws` on mount
- Auto-reconnects every 3s on disconnect
- Shows "disconnected" banner only after 5s of disconnect (avoids flicker)
- Heartbeat via ping/pong (server sends ping every 30s)

### Query Invalidation

On `data-updated` WebSocket events, the hook invalidates all TanStack queries except configuration-related ones:

```typescript
void queryClient.invalidateQueries({
  predicate: query => !['config', 'systemHealth', 'rpProjects'].includes(query.queryKey[0] as string),
});
```

### Progress Listeners

Components subscribe to progress events via dedicated hooks:
- `usePollProgress()` -- pipeline poll progress
- `useJenkinsProgress()` -- Jenkins enrichment progress
- `useSyncProgress()` -- repository sync progress

