## 13. Page Conventions

### Standard Page Structure

```tsx
export const MyPage = () => {
  useEffect(() => { document.title = 'My Page | CNV Console Monitor'; }, []);

  const { data, isLoading, error } = useQuery({ ... });

  if (isLoading) {
    return <PageSection isFilled><Spinner /></PageSection>;
  }
  if (error) {
    return <PageSection><EmptyState icon={ExclamationCircleIcon}>Error</EmptyState></PageSection>;
  }
  if (!data?.length) {
    return <PageSection><EmptyState>No data</EmptyState></PageSection>;
  }

  return (
    <>
      <PageSection variant="light"><Title headingLevel="h1">My Page</Title></PageSection>
      <PageSection>{/* content */}</PageSection>
    </>
  );
};
```

### Lazy Loading

All pages use `React.lazy` in `App.tsx` for code splitting:

```tsx
const MyPage = React.lazy(() =>
  import('./pages/MyPage').then(m => ({ default: m.MyPage })),
);
```

Wrapped in `<Suspense fallback={<Spinner />}>` at the route level.

### Adding a New Page

1. Create `pages/MyPage.tsx` with the standard structure above
2. Add lazy import in `App.tsx`
3. Add `<Route path="/my-page" element={<MyPage />} />` in `App.tsx`
4. Add navigation item in `components/layout/AppSidebar.tsx`
